The biggest prayer gathering that South Africa has ever seen began on Saturday, reports the Bloemfontein Courant.Picture: Bloemfontein CourantWell-known local Evangelist preacher Angus Buchan preached at the Wilde Als farm in Bloemfontein where more than one million people were expected to attend.Picture: Bloemfontein CourantThe prayer session officially started after 1pm, after it was initially delayed to make provision for all the people arriving late.Picture: Bloemfontein CourantListen to Buchan address the masses:&nbsp;&nbsp;Picture: Bloemfontein Courant Caxton News ServiceRead original story on www.bloemfonteincourant.co.za